HEADWORD: Tracheobronchial
<hw>Tra`che*o*bron"chi*al</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos>
<fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>Pertaining both to the tracheal and bronchial
tubes, or to their junction; -- said of the syrinx of certain
birds.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Tracheocele</ent>⟦br⟧
